name: Stranded /ˈastrənɔːt/
description: “One meaning of a "blood moon" is based on its red glow. This blood moon occurs during a total lunar eclipse. During a total lunar eclipse, Earth lines up between the Moon and the Sun” (NASA, 2019). Alone and stuck. What was bright now trapped with a little light shun from the Sun. Looking down from high up, praying for a light, a hope, an escape. For one day, will it glow again? Sound by the Real Audio of Comet "Singing" Through Space.
